md:note.div:
Anvendt astrologi og magi
Siderne 3 til 131: Ahkam al-a'la[w]iyah min al-a'lam al-samawiyah af Faxr al-Din al-Razi
Tilegnet Abu Mozaffar Takash Khvarezm-shah (567-596 H. [1172-1200])
Siderne 132 til 450: [Lava'eh al-qamar] af Hosayn ben 'Ali al-Bayhaqi al-Kashefi (d. 910 H [1504/5])
Tilegnet Madjd al-Din Mohammad [Khvafi] (d. 899 H [1494])
Håndskriftet angiver de astrologiske krav, der skal til for at få det bedste ud af livet i mange af dets forskellige aspekter, f. eks. i hvilken position stjernerne skal stå for at man kan klippe sine negle
Kopieret før 1125 H [år 1713]
Cod. Pers. AC 41

Applied astronomy and magic
Pages 3 to 131: Ahkam al-a'la[w]iyah min al-a'lam al-samawiyah by Faxr al-Din al-Razi
Inscribed to: Abu Mozaffar Takash Khvarezm-shah (567-596 H. [1172-1200 CE])
Pages 132 to 450: [Lava'eh al-qamar] by Hosayn ben 'Ali al-Bayhaqi al-Kashefi (d. 910 H [1504/5 CE])
Inscribed to: Madjd al-Din Mohammad [Khvafi] (d. 899 H [1494 CE])
The manuscripts gives among other instructions regarding the favourable positions of the stars for performing everyday acts, e.g. cutting your nails
Copied before 1125 H [1713 CE]
Cod. Pers. AC 41
